OL,3,CCrimes against women 'being ignored'
OL,4,Cas key statistic excludes rape
OL,6,FThe ONS told ITV News the nature of
OL,7,Fsexual offences means the number of
OL,8,Fthose crimes can be difficult to
OL,9,Fmeasure when estimating the UK total,
OL,10,Fso they are counted in a different way.
OL,12,FWhen working out the UK's "total"
OL,13,Fcrimes, the ONS carries out surveys
OL,14,Fand face-to-face interviews to
OL,15,Fextrapolate a figure - because not all
OL,16,Fcrimes are reported to police - but
OL,17,Fthat excludes many crimes mostly
OL,18,Fcarried out against women.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/13
