OL,6,F"In face-to-face interviews, victims -
OL,7,Fmost commonly women - can be unwilling
OL,8,Fto respond if their abuser is in the
OL,9,Froom or if their family is unaware of
OL,10,Fprevious abuse. Sometimes the abuse is
OL,11,Fongoing, often it won't have been
OL,12,Freported to police.
OL,14,F"These and other factors mean that
OL,15,Finstead of publishing total numbers of
OL,16,Fincidents, we focus on how prevalent
OL,17,Fthe crimes are - or the number of
OL,18,Fvictims - and provide in depth
OL,19,Fanalysis to give a fair reflection of
OL,20,Fthe nature of these offences."
